8 AS INTRODUCED
9 A Concurrent Resolution urging Oklahoma's
Congressional Delegation to Support the Credit for
10 Caring Act for family caregivers.
11
12
13 WHEREAS, family caregivers play a vital role in supporting loved
14 ones with long-term health needs, often bearing significant
15 financial and emotional burdens as they provide essential care; and
16 WHEREAS, the Credit for Caring Act seeks to provide a federal
17 tax credit of up to $5,000 annually to working family caregivers,
18 helping to offset the high costs of caregiving and alleviating
19 financial strain; and
20 WHEREAS, Oklahoma is home to an estimated 490,000 family
21 caregivers who collectively contribute over $6.6 billion in unpaid
22 care, providing critical support that allows many older Oklahomans
23 to remain in his or her home rather than move to costly
24 institutional care facilities; and
